Load Test Results

Load test run against http://banff.rstudio.com/content/3. The load test target was 400 total visits with 400 concurrent users at a time. Concurrent user sessions were staggered, with a max delay of 20 seconds. Each “user” ran a series of actions against the application as recorded in ./tests/myloadtest.R.

A baseline test was run with 10 total visits occuring sequentially, one at a time.

Results

The load test was started at 2017-07-18 23:00:53 and ended at 2017-07-18 23:03:55. Of the targetted 400 visits, 375 were successful.

A maximum 343 concurrent connections were achieved, compared to the target of 400.

Comparison to Baseline

The average page load time under load was 42.5226667 seconds compared to 1.9 seconds with no concurrent load.

The following graph shows the response time for specific events taken after page load. The table lists any events that did not trigger an update pior to the default timeout. For inputs that do not trigger an output (i.e. applications that use action buttons) this is expected behavior.

R Processes

Application latency is often the result of too many users sharing the same R process. RStudio Connect and Shiny Server Pro allow users to be spread across multiple R processes for any application.
